'''Meshaal Essa Barsham''' ({{langx|ar|مَشْعَل عِيسَى بَرْشَم}}; born 14 February 1998) is a football player who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Al Sadd SC|Al Sadd]]. Born in Sudan, he plays for the [[Qatar national football team|Qatar national team]].

==Club career==
===Al Sadd===
On 27 August 2018, in the [[2018 AFC Champions League knockout stage#Quarter-finals|2018 AFC Champions League quarter-finals]], Barsham started in Al Sadd's 3–1 away win against [[Esteghlal F.C.|Esteghlal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/asian-football/afc-champions-league/933570/al-sadd-overcome-comical-own-goal-to-outmuscle-esteghlal/|title=Al Sadd overcome comical own-goal to outmuscle Esteghlal|publisher=Fox Sports Asia|author=Gabriel Tan|date=27 August 2018|accessdate=27 August 2018|archive-date=28 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180828122932/https://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/asian-football/afc-champions-league/933570/al-sadd-overcome-comical-own-goal-to-outmuscle-esteghlal/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

==Personal life==
He is the younger brother of Olympic gold [[high jump]] medalist [[Mutaz Barsham]], and [[Muamer Aissa Barsham]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.qatar-tribune.com/news-details/id/226067/meshaal-barsham-does-his-sporting-family-proud|title=Meshaal Barsham does his sporting family proud|publisher=Qatar Tribune|date=20 December 2021|accessdate=27 December 2021|archive-date=27 December 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211227102749/https://www.qatar-tribune.com/news-details/id/226067/meshaal-barsham-does-his-sporting-family-proud|url-status=live}}</ref>

